In Python, `re.match` with `$` matches before a trailing newline character. So a value like `'bar
'` (a trailing LF with no subsequent text) will satisfy the pattern `^\S[^
]*$` because `$` anchors before the final `
`. Use `\Z` instead of `$` to anchor strictly at the end of the string: `r'^\S[^
]*\Z|\Z'`.

